				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Thanks for the encouragement SoleGoose, I appreciate it!<br /><br />I've been working on a roster screen that allows the player to assemble a team of 3 mechs, being able to choose the mech type, the pilot and 2 equipment slots. It works, but I still need to implement selection restrictions, e.g a pilot should can only be assigned once and unique equipment.<br /><br />I've also included a JUMP action for the lightest mech available (GEIST) allowing to move over obstacles and gaps. Additionally, a unit that jumped will be better at evading attacks until its next turn, at the expense of generating a heat point and reducing its own accuracy<br /><br />I have also revised many of the rules around damage / to hit percentages. I took inspiration from the table top game ALPHA STRIKE, i.e., instead of having several weapons that you'd need to toggle and figure out (= not fun), the game now uses the a single damage profile per unit indicating how much damage it can inflict at different ranges. <br /><br />The damage profile of a unit can be improved by equipping it with items or weapons, e.g., adding a â€˜machine gunâ€™ weapon to your unit improves damage to targets that are positioned 2 or 3 hexes from the attacking unit.<br /><br />This allows for different units with specialized roles, like close combat mechs vs long range fire support, while keeping the complexity towards the player at bay. I also like that it makes movement far more relevant.<br /><br />Next I will be improving the AIâ€™s actions and many other loose ends, before moving on to the meta game â€“ which involves moving from one mission to the next, XP points, gaining of items and all of that.</div>

					
						<br clear="all" /><br />

